Edo State will begin the hunt for fresh talent as it hosts the state’s handball league between January 20 and 22 at the University of Benin Sports Complex, Ugbowo. Chairman of the state handball association Barrister Emma Akhigbe said the championship is being organised by Edo State Handball Veterans Association. Akhigbe said that seven teams (four male and three female) have registered for the event as others are expected to join the fray before the tournament begins.   Reform Sports to renovate  Lafia Stadium     AfCON 2021: Keep winning, Buhari tells Super Eagles     BREAKING: Nigeria beat Guinea Bissau 2-0   He said: “The tournament will enable us identify players that will join the team for the forthcoming National Division One Handball League, which the state is hosting in February. - Advertisement - “It will also give the players the opportunity to showcase their skills and acquire new ones as the watch other play,” he added. The Edo State Handball boss also said that awards would be presented to the Deputy Governor, Comrade  Philip Shaibu,  President of Handball Federation of Nigeria (HFN) Samuel Ocheho, Vice President of HFN, Bala Bodinga, Vice Chancellor of UNIBEN, Prof Lilian Salami, Mrs Rose Oriaran-Anthony and Mr Monday Osagiede for their contributions to the game of handball.